Noisy motel. Fight above me in room 234 and cops were called by management to break it up. Room was clean but just bare essentials. No microwave or fridge. No coffee available in office when I visited. There has to be a better place for the money in town the next time I pass through!

Two night business trip
Overall an average experience.  Pros were a large room with microwave and larger mini fridge, nice breakfast area, nice courtyard and pool, proximity to highway and eating choices in walking distance.  Cons were noise (room on street side), Keurig machine did not work in room, room had no real dresser for clothes, and the furniture needed updating, and personal preference the bed was too firm for my liking,  Would stay again for the convenience but among HIE properties this was just average overall.

Fantastic service, clean rooms, great smoothies!
We stopped here because we were going to spend the day at Six Flags. My son got a fever just before check-in, so we ended up spending two days/nights just hanging out in the hotel. I ran around a lot, getting food for the sick boy and taking care of stuff - and this place is close to lots of quick food, which is all my son wanted to eat. And during all my up-and-down, in-and-out lobby visits, staff was friendly, professional and helpful.  If my son had to get sick during our LA vacation, I'm so glad it happened here! Room was immaculate and modern with comfortable beds and no noise (except when someone passed in the hallway). We had GREAT service in every way - and I especially loved the breakfast smoothies!

Budget room for budget price
Booked last minute as flight changed and needed to be close to airport/car rentals. Check in was quick and staff were friendly. Room was clean but dated. Beds were comfortable. Pool was small but good enough for a dip to cool down.  No tea/coffee facilities in room. No safe in room. Very noisy ( no double glazing) but air con ok. Area a little run down. There is an airport shuttle bus but be prepared to wait (45 minutes for us) was just sorting out taxis when it arrived.  It‚Äôs good enough for some to sleep on a budget whilst waiting for flight, but no more than that.

Good Stay One Night

In comparison to the Holiday Inn Express in Carpinteria, everything is bigger and better, the room, the pool area and the breakfast. Curiously, neither place had potatoes in the breakfast, and each had both pork and turkey sausage.  But the breakfast here was well stocked with many choices, including real oatmeal and a pancake machine.  The breakfast room is spacious.

Not up to standards even for a mid range hotel
Actually surprised at this hotel is still an approved Holiday Inn Express franchise. It's a very old property and reminds me of the hotels along the interstate when you travel from state to state. The doors open to the parking lot there was a lot of traffic noise and the room has the old adjoining thin doors between the rooms I could hear the TV in the next room for about an hour after I went to bed. .  On the plus side, the staff is very helpful and they do the best with what they are given. The room and gym were very clean and the breakfast met the standard Holiday Inn Express breakfast. West Coast Trip
My wife and I planned this trip in order to be able to visit her brother, as well as my brother, both of which live in the general San Fransisco area.  Upon arriving we found the area around the not as bright and welcoming as we had hoped.  We were made aware of the unfortunate vast number of homeless in the San Fransisco area.  Unfortunately the hotel is located in the immediate area of a number of homeless.  Once inside the hotel lobby was comfortably furnished.  Our room was on the sixth floor, which we were told was assigned to us to lessen the street noise, we appreciated having a very late check-in. We soon found out this was definitely needed as the hotel does not have air conditioning, requiring us to sleep with the window open and the box fan provided in the room

No air conditioning. Noisy homeless people in the streets make sleeping impossible
The room is not air conditioned, but don't even think of opening the window. The homeless people on the street below are noisy and the area is filled with drug addicts. Terrible service at breakfast. We booked on Hotwire.com, where the hotel was billed as four star - not even close! Bring ear plugs or noise reduction headphones, and make sure the fan in the closet is working to keep cool. The description on hotwire.com was very misleading.

Second review -- because no AC during a heat wave, and no refrigerator, is just unacceptable
I stayed at this hotel in March of 2019. At that time, the street noise was the issue and the hotel's response to my comments then was that "noise" was dependent on each individual's sensitivity. I never bothered to tell them that loud garbage trucks in the middle of the night would exceed anyone's tolerance for noise.  But here I am in late September, and it is over 90 degrees Fahrenheit outside, and this room is a furnace! HOW is it possible that in 2019 a hotel in the middle of a major US city does not have air conditioning, nor a refrigerator to keep bottled water cooled in a room? I never turned on the television -- you can promptly replace that with a refrigerator! Meanwhile, the staff tells me the building is over 100 years old and is not outfitted for air conditioning

Perfect location spoilt only by the noisy homeless people in the nearby street
Ideally situated for Westfield shopping and Union Square. Stunning decor inside the hotel. We had a twin room which was big enough for our needs. Double glazing is required in the next refurbishment as the noise from the homeless people adjacent to the hotel goes on through the night and does disturb. Ear plugs are provided but this isn‚Äôt an ideal solution. The two ladies on reception on 24th November 2019 and 1st December 2019 along with everyone else (with the exception of one who I will detail further down the review) were superb and very courteous and polite. The free coffee and tea in reception is a nice touch and we utilised it more than once. There are several diners nearby that offer a full cooked breakfast which were reasonably priced. Just ok

Room was clean but felt dated and very small. Bathroom was nice. No air con was a nightmare as it was very hot, there was a small fan but was very noisy. WiFi in room was practically non existent and very annoying. Very noisy all through the night. Homeless all around union square and the hotel. Fabulous shops in union square and cable cars very close to hotel. We also walked to tourist places, exploring painted ladies, fisherman‚Äôs wharf, pier 39, Mrs Doubtfire house, Lombard street etc. took about 45 mins or so. Had a great time in San Francisco but we wouldn‚Äôt stay at this hotel again.

It ticked all my boxes.
I arrived around nine at night having without a reservation, having driven from the Inland empire on my way to the Mexico border. I needed a motel near the airport so i could return the rented car and then take the metro to the border.   The Motel is  at the end of the runway on the other side of the fence and planes literally skim the roof on landing, it is an experience to behold, I loved it it it was like being on a movie set. I only stayed a night and my room was clean enough. Given its location you would expectit to have been really noisy, but I did not find this to be the case. Sure I could feel the downdraft from the planes kind of like skock waves, but as i was only staying one night i enjoyed the novelty.  I would certainly recommend the experience.

Great customer service. Friendly and helpful staff. They were always very accommodating and quick to respond. Great restaurant for dinner with good wine (it‚Äôs expensive tho).
